0.\n\nbhiyas, fear: bhiyasa, V, 59, 2; bhiyase, (I, 87, 6:1.)\n\nbhisha _g_ , physician: bhishak-tamam bhisha _g_ am, the best of all\nphysicians, II, 33, 4.\n\nbhi, to fear: bhayate, I, 166, 5; VII, 58, 2; bhayante, I, 85, 8: 166, 4;\nbibhaya, V, 60, 3; bibhyushe, I, 39, 7; abibhayanta, I, 39, 6.--See abibhivas,\nbhiyas.\n\nbhi\xc2\xb4, f., fear: bhiya\xc2\xb4, I, 37, 8; 171, 4; V, 57, 3:2; 60, 2; VIII, 7, 26.\n\nbhima, terrible: bhima\xc2\xb4 _h_ , II, 34, 1; bhi\xc2\xb4masa _h_ , VII, 58, 2; m _ri_ gam\nna bhimam, II, 33, 11:2.\n\nbhima-yu, fearful: bhima-yu _h_ , V, 56, 3.\n\nbhima-sand _ri_ _s_ , terrible to behold: bhima-sand _ri_ _s_ ah, V, 56, 2.\n\nbhu _g_ man, the feeding cloud: bhu _g_ ma\xc2\xb4, (I, 64, 3:1.)\n\nbhu _\xc3\xb1_ _g_ , to enjoy: bhu _g_ e (ishe), VIII, 20, 8; ekam it bhu _g_ e, of\nuse, VIII, 20, 13.\n\nbhurvan, whirl: bhurva _n_ i (apa\xc2\xb4m), I, 134, 5 (bis); p. cxxii.\n\nbhuvana, being, world: vi _s_ va bhuvanani, bhuvana, I, 64, 3; 85, 8; 166, 4;\nII, 34, 4; vi _s_ vasmat bhuvanat, I, 134, 5.--asya bhuvanasya bhu\xc2\xb4re _h_ , of\nthis wide world, II, 33, 9; asya vi _s_ vasya bhuvanasya ra\xc2\xb4 _g_ a (Vata), X,\n168, 2; bhuvanasya garbha _h_ , X, 168, 41.\n\nbhu, to be \xe2\x80\xa6: bhuva _h_ , I, 86, 5:1; na _h_ babhu\xc2\xb4tha, thou hast come to be\nwith us, I, 165, 5; p. xv; babhuva\xc2\xb4n, having grown, I, 165, 8; _s_ am na _h_\nbhutam, VI, 74, 1; ([190](sbe3226.htm#page_190) seq.;\n[435](sbe3258.htm#page_435)); bhuvan sakam, they became full of, VI, 66, 2;\nbodhi, II, 33, 15:2.--ma\xc2\xb4 apa bhutana, do not keep away, VII, 59, 10.--ma\xc2\xb4 api\nbhuma tasyam, let us not fall under its power, VII, 57, 4:1.--kuta _h_ a\xc2\xb4\nbabhuva, whence did he spring, X, 168, 3.--pari babhuva, he embraces, X, 121,\n10.--vi-bhvane, ([48](sbe3216.htm#page_48).)--bhavya and bhuta, what is and\nwhat will be, (p. [4](sbe3215.htm#page_4)); bhutasya pati _h_ , the lord of\nall that is, X, 121, 1.\n\nbhu\xc2\xb4man, earth: bhu\xc2\xb4m